description:
&lt;p&gt;An exciting opportunity has arisen for dynamic and enthusiastic individuals to join our Clinical Administration Service Admin Bank&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Our administration team play a vital role in the delivery of patient care via the management of the patients end-to-end pathway and supporting the wider team. Our roles are varied and challenging and your day to day duties may include;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Booking and departing patients on one of our busy reception desks&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Working in our medical records departments, ensuring patient notes are available for all patient appointments&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Helping track our patients through their journey to ensure a great patient experience&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Supporting the Senior Administrators including typing of clinical correspondence and adding patients to waiting lists&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Whilst previous administration experience is desirable, we are first and foremost looking for individuals with a passion to work in a health care setting and those with a &#39;can do&#39; attitude.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The successful candidates will join a friendly and supportive team that values the contribution of all staff.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As a member of the bank your hours and working pattern will vary dependent on the assignment but the majority of our working patterns are between the hours of 08.00-20.00&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Should you wish to discuss this opportunity further, please get in touch.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Philip.Collins@hey.nhs.uk&lt;/p&gt;
